			
			JTMOS BLOCK DEVICE API


(Device Call #)
	01		DEVICE_INIT
	02		DEVICE_SHUTDOWN
	03		DEVICE_READBLOCK
	04		DEVICE_WRITEBLOCK
	05		NONE
	06		DEVICE_GETSIZE
	07		DEVICE_GETBLOCKSIZE
	08		DEVICE_SEEK
	09		DEVICE_GETCH
	0A		DEVICE_PUTCH
	...and more...
	(see dcpacket.h)


Prototype:

	DEVICE_CALL device_call_nr, option1, option2, option3, option4,
			pointer1,pointer2

Ways to implement:

	DEVICE_CALL [DEVICE_INIT], 0,0,0,0, NULL,NULL
	
	DEVICE_CALL [DEVICE_SHUTDOWN], 0,0,0,0, NULL,NULL

	DEVICE_CALL [DEVICE_READBLOCK], WHICH_BLOCK, 0,0,0,
			FILE *,BYTE *buffer

	...And so on...














